---

# Automated Backup Infrastructure Deployment (Ansible)

This repository provides an **automated deployment framework** for two secure backup architectures:

* **Rsnapshot + GPG encryption**
* **Rsnapshot + LUKS disk encryption with hardlink deduplication**

The infrastructure is deployed automatically using **Ansible**, simulating a cloud deployment scenario similar to provisioning servers on providers such as **Hetzner**.

Instead of using real VPS instances, this project reproduces the same workflow using **virtual machines** running on **Proxmox / Ludus**.

---

# Architecture Overview

![Infrastructure Architecture](architecture.png)

The deployment infrastructure contains:

* **Ansible Controller (vmcontrol)**
* **Target Server 1 – GPG Backup**
* **Target Server 2 – LUKS Backup**

The controller connects to the servers via **SSH** and automatically deploys the backup environments.

---

# Infrastructure Components

### Ansible Controller (vmcontrol)

Responsible for:

* running the Ansible container
* executing the deployment playbooks
* connecting to remote servers via SSH
* cloning and deploying backup projects

---

### Target Server – GPG Backup

Runs the **rsnapshot + GPG backup architecture**.

Characteristics:

* file-level encryption using **GPG**
* encrypted archives generated on client side
* rsnapshot retrieves encrypted archives
* deduplication is not possible due to encryption entropy

---

### Target Server – LUKS Backup

Runs the **rsnapshot + LUKS backup architecture**.

Characteristics:

* disk-level encryption using **LUKS**
* rsnapshot pulls raw files via SSH
* filesystem hardlink deduplication enabled
* optimized disk usage

---

# Target Machine Preparation

Freshly cloned virtual machines may share the same `machine-id`, which can cause network conflicts.

Regenerate it before deployment:

```bash
sudo rm /etc/machine-id
sudo systemd-machine-id-setup
sudo reboot
```

---

# SSH Configuration

The deployment assumes an environment similar to **cloud VPS providers such as Hetzner**, where administrative access is performed using **root SSH login**.

Edit:

```
/etc/ssh/sshd_config
```

Enable:

```
PermitRootLogin yes
PasswordAuthentication yes
PubkeyAuthentication yes
```

Restart SSH:

```bash
systemctl restart ssh
```

---

# SSH Key Distribution

From the **Ansible controller machine**, copy the SSH public key to the target machines.

```bash
ssh-copy-id -i ssh_keys/id_rsa.pub root@vmtargetx
ssh-copy-id -i ssh_keys/id_rsa.pub root@vmtargety
```

---

# Inventory Configuration

Edit the Ansible inventory file:

```ini
[app]
vmtargetx
vmtargety
```

These machines will receive the automated deployment.

---

# Deployment

Make the deployment script executable:

```bash
chmod +x deploy.sh
```

Run the deployment:

```bash
./deploy.sh
```

The deployment will automatically:

* start the Ansible container
* run the master playbook
* install required packages
* install Docker
* clone backup repositories
* start the containerized backup infrastructure

---

# Installation Paths on Target Machines

Once the deployment is complete, the backup infrastructures will be installed in the following locations:

```
/opt/rsnapshot-gpg
/opt/rsnapshot-luks
```

Each directory contains the full Docker-based backup environment.

---

# Verification

Connect to a target server:

```bash
ssh root@vmtargetluks
```

Navigate to the project directory:

```bash
cd /opt/rsnapshot-luks
```

Verify running containers:

```bash
docker ps
```

Run a backup test:

```bash
docker exec -it backup rsnapshot alpha
```

---

# Related Backup Projects

This repository focuses on **automating the deployment** of the backup infrastructures.

The full backup implementations can be found in the following repositories:

### Rsnapshot + LUKS (disk encryption)

[https://github.com/TsamD/rsnapshot-luks.git](https://github.com/TsamD/rsnapshot-luks.git)

### Rsnapshot + GPG (file encryption)

[https://github.com/TsamD/backup_rsnapshot.git](https://github.com/TsamD/backup_rsnapshot.git)

These repositories contain:

* detailed architecture diagrams
* backup workflows
* restore procedures
* deeper explanations of encryption and deduplication mechanisms.

